The proscribed Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB has been called out by a former militant leader, Asari Dokubo.  Dokubo accused the Indigenous People of Biafra of being a satanic movement. He took to his Facebook page on Sunday, 30th January 2022 to make the allegation. Recall that he had some days ago condemned the sit-at-home order imposed on the Southeast by IPOB, saying it is crippling the economy of the region. Speaking today on Facebook live, he said: “IPOB is not just a terrorist organization, IPOB is worse than a terrorist organization; IPOB is a satanic movement.” This comes as the group is accused of engaging in cannibalism. Watch video below: •Asari Dokubo and Nnamdi Kanu Agitation for an independent state of Biafra suffered a setback Friday with a former Niger Delta militant leader, Asari Dokubo describing the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) Nnamdi Kanu, as an “idiot.” Asari, a former leader of the Niger Delta People’s Volunteer… In "News" A former Niger Delta militant, Asari Dokubo, has mocked Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, over his re-arrest by the federal government, Daily Post reports. Recall that Dokubo had vowed to destroy Kanu, who he described as ‘evil’ and also accused him of defrauding Biafrans. In… In "News" The Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) has maintained that the group would not be intimidated by the threat by the new Acting Inspector General of police (IGP), Alkali Usman of a clamp-down on its members and other pro-Biafra activists. The new police boss had on Thursday vowed to “confront increasingly,… In "News"